\,\mathbf r(0)=(x_0,y_0)
\,\dot{\mathbf r}(0)=(v_{x,0},v_{y,0})
$\begin{align}  r_i &=\sqrt{x_i^2+y_i^2} \\ \\ v_{x,i+1} &=v_{x,i}-\frac {GMx_i}{r_i^3}\Delta t \\ \\v_{y,i+1} &=v_{y,i}-\frac {GMy_i}{r_i^3}\Delta t \\ \\x_{i+1} &=x_i+v_{x,i+1}\Delta t \\ \\y_{i+1} &=y_i+v_{y,i+1}\Delta t \\ \\\end{align}
